[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man hit by lorry dies in Greenwich 'hit-and-run' crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man died when he was struck by a lorry in an apparent hit-and-run crash in Greenwich.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The pedestrian, said by police to be in his 50s, was pronounced dead at the scene in Bugsby's Way at about 15:00 GMT.
Officers want to speak to the driver of a silver lorry that drove away following the incident.
The victim has not been formally identified, though his next of kin have been informed, police said.
